Bash script generating a self-executable script containing encrypted user
configuration files, system configuration files and an arbitrary directory of files
here called "essentials".

Usage:
1) List in user_conf the files/folders you want from the user
2) List in system_conf the folders you want from the filesystem (where you have root privileges)
3) Edit packager.sh and set "/data/essential" to whatever directory you want
4) sh packager.sh
5) follow instructions

This code is licensed under MIT/X11

This code might be useful as an example of making self-executables for Linux
